<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="339" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,151,465]" pageId="8" pageNumber="339">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,403,429]" pageId="8" pageNumber="339">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epither is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[851,985,403,428]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="339">parvissimus</emphasis>
, referring to the small uncus of the male genitalia.
</paragraph>
